    "question_id" : 854264,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>In Intellij 13, it looks it's slightly different again. Here are the instructions for Intellij 13:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>click on the Project view or unhide it by clicking on the \"1: Project\" button on the left border of the window or by pressing Alt + 1</li>\n<li>find your project or sub-module and click on it to highlight it, then press F4, or right click and choose \"Open Module Settings\" (on IntelliJ 14 it became F12)</li>\n<li>click on the dependencies tab</li>\n<li>Click the \"+\" button on the right and select \"Jars or directories...\"</li>\n<li>Find your path and click OK</li>\n<li>In the dialog with \"Choose Categories of Selected File\", choose <code>Classes</code> (even if it's properties), press OK and OK again</li>\n<li>You can now run your application and it will have the selected path in the class path </li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5934605,
      "reputation" : 147,
      "user_id" : 4668045,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/yTggJ.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "VNN456",
